I've been searching the net up and down for any and all information regarding the display unit of the original NES. The information gathered from various sources, have turned out to be rather poor and lacking.<br /><br />So, the deal is the following: I've got a M82. The unit's got plenty of games (9-10 games or such), and the unit is working. -ish. See, the M82's got a knob on the back where the store supervisor or such is supposed to choose between 30 secs, 3 minutes, 6 minutes or 120 minutes. That knob is broken. so the console is stuck at 30 sec 'game play', then reboots and shows the game-list.<br /><br />Ideally, I'd disable the reboot sequence al together. I realize this might be hard/impossible to do without major changes to the system, but any pointers in this direction would be greatly appreciated.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=262">Gilrim</a> — Mon Dec 12, 2005 5:17 am</p><hr />
